WEBVTT

00:00:00.940 --> 00:00:07.440
Think back for a moment on how Jehovah supported his organization in ancient times.

00:00:07.440 --> 00:00:09.919
One example is Bezileu.

00:00:09.919 --> 00:00:11.720
Do you remember him?

00:00:11.720 --> 00:00:15.720
Jehovah appointed him to make furnishings for the tabernacle.

00:00:15.720 --> 00:00:18.039
That's quite a responsibility.

00:00:18.039 --> 00:00:21.160
But what experience did Bezileu have?

00:00:21.160 --> 00:00:24.559
His last job was making bricks in Egypt.

00:00:24.559 --> 00:00:29.219
While it is possible he had some other skills, how would he accomplish something as grand

00:00:29.219 --> 00:00:31.739
as the tabernacle?

00:00:31.739 --> 00:00:38.179
Exodus chapter 35 teaches us that it was Jehovah, that gave Bezileu the wisdom and the

00:00:38.179 --> 00:00:41.299
understanding to do the work.

00:00:41.299 --> 00:00:45.340
Jehovah's earthly organization today faces similar challenges.

00:00:45.340 --> 00:00:50.780
The brothers that took the lead in setting up our first primary had no prior experience.

00:00:50.780 --> 00:00:55.179
And the same applies to brothers that produced our very first video.

00:00:55.179 --> 00:01:00.380
You will enjoy this archive interview with Brother Lyman Swingle, who was part of that

00:01:00.380 --> 00:01:02.859
very first video team.

00:01:02.859 --> 00:01:07.019
Brother Swingle was later appointed as a member of the governing body until he finished

00:01:07.019 --> 00:01:11.140
his earthly course in 2001.

